This paper deals with natural language generation and machine translation, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural models for multi-task learning is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for formality transfer, which is a sub-topic of natural language processing that involves sentiment analysis and text classification (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks for style transfer, which is a sub-topic of computer vision that involves image-to-image translation (cs.SD).
